On my mind…..

I’ve been thinking about how the biggest and best goals we set for ourselves require tens of thousands, maybe millions, of seemingly minute choices, to slowly accumulate into drastic life changes or results. 

Whether your goal is physical, mental or emotional the same logic applies: it’s a shifting of habits, a new wake up time, a daily ritual that takes 2 minutes or 1 hour of your day, sustained over a long period of time, and then finally, after months or even years, if you can stick with it long enough, you find yourself at new place in your life, and hopefully take the time to feel good about how far you’ve come.

But by the time you arrive there, the funny part is, it doesn’t feel that grand. Along the journey, you’ve broken old patterns and in order to break old patterns you’re forced to create new ones. In all the days, weeks, months and years since you set out on this journey, you start to see yourself differently as you  adopt new ways of thinking or acting. 

We aren’t defined by the finish line; We are defined by the journey. So every time your efforts feel fruitless, or the path seems interminable, remember that there is a version of you way down the line that you wouldn’t even recognize. Think of how many times you’ve already rose from the ashes to rebuild a new you because your life required you do so. 

Keep moving, keep chasing, keep doing those mundane tasks that WILL add up to something so amazing, because it is impossible not to be rewarded for consistent, directed and focused effort. 

🌹❤️
